DEXTERITY

Dexterity is a measure of your agility and flexibility, and is
actually one of the most flexible and versatile attributes, showing
up in many places.  It plays into success rates for numerous skills,
including conceal, sneak, instant kill, disarm, corner, hide, and
steal.  It also helps determine how much damage lay hands does.

Of course, dexterity plays an integral role in combat.  High
dexterity values also help lower your AC.  It helps your chance to
flee.  Perhaps most importantly, dexterity plays directly into the
hit-miss calculations, helping you dodge, parry, and ripost your
enemy's attacks.  Your dexterity attribute helps you stay standing
when someone casts earthquake, too.

Dexterity plays a small part in determining your wand and breath
saves.  It also determines how many items you can carry at your
level.

See also: ATTRIBUTE, SCORE, AC
