GUILDS CLANS

Guilds are groupings of like-minded people who have written a formal 
declaration of intent to the mud's administration which has been accepted
for use. Guilds get some very important bonuses: They get their own global
communication channel (see CTELL), their own guild house (see GUILD), and
occasionally even their own shops and gear. This comes at a price: Guilds
are expensive to start and maintain, and every one of these perks are ungodly
expensive too.

Probably the hardest aspect of being a guild is that gods consider guilds
free game for bothering with roleplay and quests.

Clans are pretty much like guilds in terms of game mechanics, but instead
of being restricted by class, alignment, or race, are generally family
groupings of one specific race (like, the Bonechewer troll clan).

Zzur's got an absolutely huge text document on these things that he'll
happily email you if you ask. His email is zzur@fierymud.org  :)

