INNATE
 
Usage: innate
       innate <effect>
 
This command lists the innate skills and effects available for your race.
Innate skills can be used at any time, and are marked with a * symbol on the
list.  Innate effects are like special spells.  Some innate effects are
always present on you and are also marked with a * symbol.  Innate effects
on the list without a * are limited in duration and can only be used once in
a while.  You can invoke these by typing "innate <effect>", where effect is
the name of the innate effect.
 
For instance, Half-Elves have innate infravision always present, so they can
see in the dark all the time.  Dwarves have innate strength, but it is not
always present, so to invoke it they would simply type "innate strength".
Much like magic spells, innate effects that are not always present cannot
be invoked in rooms where magic is suppressed.
 
